# Padroes de Teste Svelte (Svelte Testing Library)

## Estrutura Base

```ts
import { render, screen } from "@testing-library/svelte";
import { fireEvent } from "@testing-library/dom";
import Button from "./Button.svelte";

describe("Button", () => {
  it("renderiza com texto correto", () => {
    render(Button, { props: { children: "Salvar" } });
    expect(screen.getByRole("button", { name: "Salvar" })).toBeInTheDocument();
  });

  it("chama onclick ao clicar", async () => {
    const onclick = vi.fn();
    render(Button, { props: { onclick } });

    await fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole("button"));
    expect(onclick).toHaveBeenCalledOnce();
  });
});
```

## Renderizando com Props

```ts
render(Button, {
  props: {
    variant: "outline",
    size: "lg",
    disabled: true,
  },
});
```

## Testando Reatividade

```ts
import { render, screen } from "@testing-library/svelte";
import { fireEvent } from "@testing-library/dom";

it("incrementa contador ao clicar", async () => {
  render(Counter);

  const button = screen.getByRole("button");
  expect(screen.getByText("0")).toBeInTheDocument();

  await fireEvent.click(button);
  expect(screen.getByText("1")).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

## Testando Slots/Snippets

```ts
import { render } from "@testing-library/svelte";
import CardWrapper from "./CardWrapper.test.svelte";

// Criar componente wrapper de teste para snippets complexos
it("renderiza conteudo do snippet", () => {
  render(CardWrapper);
  expect(screen.getByText("Conteudo do Card")).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

## Cleanup

```ts
import { cleanup } from "@testing-library/svelte";

afterEach(() => {
  cleanup();
});
```

## Convencoes

- Usar `@testing-library/svelte` para render e screen
- Usar `@testing-library/dom` para fireEvent
- Props passadas no objeto `props`
- Criar componentes wrapper `.test.svelte` para snippets complexos
- Sempre fazer cleanup apos cada teste
- Queries por role/text (mesma prioridade do Testing Library)
