# Svelte Testing Patterns (Svelte Testing Library)

## Base Structure

```ts
import { render, screen } from "@testing-library/svelte";
import { fireEvent } from "@testing-library/dom";
import Button from "./Button.svelte";

describe("Button", () => {
  it("renders with correct text", () => {
    render(Button, { props: { children: "Save" } });
    expect(screen.getByRole("button", { name: "Save" })).toBeInTheDocument();
  });

  it("calls onclick when clicked", async () => {
    const onclick = vi.fn();
    render(Button, { props: { onclick } });

    await fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole("button"));
    expect(onclick).toHaveBeenCalledOnce();
  });
});
```

## Rendering with Props

```ts
render(Button, {
  props: {
    variant: "outline",
    size: "lg",
    disabled: true,
  },
});
```

## Testing Reactivity

```ts
import { render, screen } from "@testing-library/svelte";
import { fireEvent } from "@testing-library/dom";

it("increments counter on click", async () => {
  render(Counter);

  const button = screen.getByRole("button");
  expect(screen.getByText("0")).toBeInTheDocument();

  await fireEvent.click(button);
  expect(screen.getByText("1")).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

## Testing Slots/Snippets

```ts
import { render } from "@testing-library/svelte";
import CardWrapper from "./CardWrapper.test.svelte";

// Create test wrapper component for complex snippets
it("renders snippet content", () => {
  render(CardWrapper);
  expect(screen.getByText("Card Content")).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

## Cleanup

```ts
import { cleanup } from "@testing-library/svelte";

afterEach(() => {
  cleanup();
});
```

## Conventions

- Use `@testing-library/svelte` for render and screen
- Use `@testing-library/dom` for fireEvent
- Props passed in the `props` object
- Create `.test.svelte` wrapper components for complex snippets
- Always cleanup after each test
- Query by role/text (same Testing Library priority)
